The paper discusses the adoption of machine learning in high-stakes applications and proposes an approach to generate explanations that are comprehensible to domain users. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on the human-computer interaction aspect of generating explanations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of augmented data to generate explanations, which suggests that it may belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on multiple datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
